The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Vogts to take Nigeria job 

Berlin: Former Germany coach Berti Vogts is to take charge of Nigerias national team, according to a German newspaper. 

Vogts, who led Germany to victory at Euro 96 and also had spells in charge of Kuwait and Scotland, would take over on March 1 on a contract running until 2010, the report said. 

Its a great challenge, the 60-year-old Vogts was quoted as saying in a report released to the media ahead of publication. 

Im wildly happy, he added. 

 (REUTERS) 




